The prior probabilities part tells us the probability of a random sample being part of a certain group. Here we have:

\[ \begin{array}{ll} p(0) = 0.64\ &(Not\ purchased)\\ p(1) = 0.36\ &(Purchased) \end{array} \]

The group means part tells us the mean of a feature of a particular group. Here we have:

Age EstimatedSalary
0 -0.4720458 -0.2369546
1 0.8514471 0.4274041

Accuracy comparison

accuracy = function(cm){
    return ((cm[1]+cm[4])/sum(cm))
}
accuracy_logreg = accuracy(cm)
accuracy_lda = accuracy(cm.lda)
accuracy_logreg
## [1] 0.82
accuracy_lda
## [1] 0.81

We see that we have a better accuracy with the logistic regression than with the linear discrimiant analysis.

LDA from scratch

Question 10

  1. Subset the training set
class0 = subset(training_set,Purchased==0)
class1 = subset(training_set,Purchased==1)
  1. Computation of \(\pi_0\) and \(pi_1\)
N_0 = nrow(class0)
N_1 = nrow(class1)
N = nrow(training_set)

pi_0 = N_0/N
pi_1 = N_1/N
  1. Computation of \(\mu_0 = \begin{pmatrix}\mu_0(X_1)\\\mu_0(X_2)\end{pmatrix}\) and \(\mu_1 = \begin{pmatrix}\mu_1(X_1)\\\mu_1(X_2)\end{pmatrix}\)
compute_mean_vector = function(class_){
    return (c(mean(class_$Age),mean(class_$EstimatedSalary)))
}
mu_0 = compute_mean_vector(class0)
mu_1 = compute_mean_vector(class1)
mu_0
## [1] -0.4720458 -0.2369546
mu_1
## [1] 0.8514471 0.4274041
  1. Computation of \(\Sigma\)
compute_big_sigma = function(cov0,cov1,N_0,N_1){
    return ( ( (N_0-1)*cov0 + (N_1-1)*cov1 )/(N_0+N_1-2) )
}
cov0 = cov(class0[c(1,2)])
cov1 = cov(class1[c(1,2)])
big_sigma = compute_big_sigma(cov0,cov1,N_0,N_1)
  1. Computaiton of the discriminant scores
compute_discriminant_score = function(x,cov_matrix,mean_matrix,pi_vector){
    return (t(x)%*%solve(cov_matrix)%*%mean_matrix-(1/2)*sum(t(mean_matrix)%*%solve(cov_matrix)%*%mean_matrix)+log(pi_vector,base=exp(1)))
}

classify = function(x,cov_matrix,mean_matrix,pi_vector){
    dsmt_0 = compute_discriminant_score(x,cov_matrix,mean_matrix[[1]],pi_vector[[1]])
    dsmt_1 = compute_discriminant_score(x,cov_matrix,mean_matrix[[2]],pi_vector[[2]])
    return (ifelse(dsmt_0 > dsmt_1,0,1))
}

classify(c(1,1.5),big_sigma,list(mu_0,mu_1),list(pi_0,pi_1))
##      [,1]
## [1,]    1
pred.lda_scratch = apply(test_set[1:2],1,function(x) classify(x,big_sigma,list(mu_0,mu_1),list(pi_0,pi_1)))

table(test_set$Purchased,pred.lda$class)
##    
##      0  1
##   0 57  7
##   1 12 24

We see that we have the same result than with the function lda

Question 14

require(ROCR)
score_glm = prediction(pred.glm,test_set[,3])
score_lda = prediction(pred.lda$posterior[,2],test_set[,3])
score_qda = prediction(pred.qda$posterior[,2],test_set[,3])
x_lda = performance(score_lda,"tpr","fpr")@x.values[[1]]
y_lda = performance(score_lda,"tpr","fpr")@y.values[[1]]

x_qda = performance(score_qda,"tpr","fpr")@x.values[[1]]
y_qda = performance(score_qda,"tpr","fpr")@y.values[[1]]

plot(performance(score_glm,"tpr","fpr"),col="seagreen")
legend(x="bottomright",
       legend=c("Linear Logistic Regression",
                  "Linear Discriminant Analysis",
                  "Quadratic Discriminant Analysis"
                  ),
       col=c("seagreen","coral","skyblue"),
       cex=0.8,
       lty=1
)
lines(x_lda,y_lda,col="coral")
lines(x_qda,y_qda,col="skyblue")
abline(0,1,lty=8)
